 This is great.

63
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,000
 So why am I doing this Christmas quiz?

64
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:40,000
 Well, what I wanted to highlight through my own experience, but also I think through our experience right now here together is that our knowledge from Christmas about Jesus, it comes from pop culture, from Christmas plays, from tradition, but not really from the biblical account.

65
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:52,000
 And so what happens over time is that these traditions, they have made Jesus into someone he is not really.

66
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,000
 They made him meek and mild.

67
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,000
 He's baby Jesus.

68
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:02,000
 And it's like I call it the tamed Jesus.

69
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,000
 It's not the Jesus of scripture.

70
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:13,000
 Where all the rough edges, all the things that might challenge us, they're, what do you call it, sanded off.

71
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:21,000
 And so it's this Jesus that we hear and learn about in pop culture, but it's not really who Jesus is.

72
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:40,000
 And what I want to do with you today is I want to take you to some of the birth narratives of Jesus where we can get a glimpse of the real Jesus, the untamed Jesus, the Jesus that has the power to change people's lives.

73
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:52,000
 The Jesus that has the power to turn our lives around and the Jesus that speaks authoritatively yet lovingly into our lives and has something to say to us.

74
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:57,000
 And so we're continuing in our message today.

